article.headline: Maine 59, New Hampshire 56 (OT)
article.story: ORONO, Maine (AP) -- Rashard Turner scored 16 points Sunday to lead Maine to an overtime 59-56 win over America East rival New Hampshire. Jermaine Anderson was the top New Hampshire scorer with 12 points. Both teams had trouble shooting from the floor. Maine (10-15, 5-9) hit only 19 of 51 field goal attempts; New Hampshire (10-16, 7-8) was 18 for 49. New Hampshire was sharp from the foul line, netting 14 of 15, while Maine made 14 of 20 free throw attempts. New Hampshire led 33-23 at intermission and by 12 early in the second half. The score was knotted at 50-50 at the end of regulation. Maine got 12 points from Phil Tchekane Bofia and 11 from Ernest Turner. Blagoj Janev and Mike Christensen each scored 11 for New Hampshire.
